JOHANNESBURG - South African, New Zealand and Australian Rugby (Sanzaar) has issued Sharks lock Ruan Botha with a warning. This after foul play in the Super Rugby match against the Highlanders at Jonsson Kings Park in Durban on Saturday. The incident occurred in the 58th minute of the match. A warning may be issued by the Sanzaar’s Citing Commissioner for foul play incidents that are very close to, but in his opinion, do not meet the Red Card threshold for citings. This is not Botha’s first brush with officials. READ: Sharks lock Botha suspended for three matches In June 2017, he was slapped with a three month suspension. African News Agency